article.headline: Ohio 78, Northern Illinois 67
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Antonio Chatman scored all of Ohio's points in a 9-0 run early in the second half to send the Bobcats to a 78-67 win over Northern Illinois on Thursday night. Leon Williams led Ohio (14-6, 8-4 Mid-American) with 20 points, Chatman finished with 14 and Jerome Tillman added 11. Ohio broke away with an 18-2 run midway through the first half, but the Huskies answered with their own 16-5 spurt to cut Ohio's lead to 36-31 at the break. The Huskies made it a three-point game to start the second half before Chatman hit two 3-pointers, a layup and a free throw to give the Bobcats a 12-point lead. Ohio never trailed and held Northern Illinois (13-8, 8-5) to 40 percent from the field in the second half. Todd Peterson led the Huskies with 17 points. Cory Sims added 14 points and 10 rebounds and Anthony Maestranzi scored 11.
